Create E2E tests for all authentication flows including Cloudflare Access.

# Auth Flows to Test

## 1. Initial Authentication
- Unauthenticated user visits protected route
- Redirect to Cloudflare Access
- OAuth flow completion
- Return to original destination
- Session cookie set

## 2. Session Persistence
- Refresh page retains auth
- New tab uses existing session
- Session survives browser restart (within limits)

## 3. Session Expiry
- Session expires after timeout
- User notified of expiry
- Graceful redirect to login
- Return to previous page after re-auth

## 4. Protected Route Access
- Lab mode routes require auth
- Public routes accessible without auth
- Partial content for unauthenticated users
- Full content after authentication

## 5. Logout Flow
- Explicit logout action
- Session invalidation
- Cookie clearing
- Redirect to public page

# Test File Structure
```typescript
// e2e/authentication.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from './utils/test-fixtures';

test.describe('Authentication', () => {
  test.describe('Protected Routes', () => {
    test('redirects unauthenticated user from lab', async ({ page, logger }) => {
      // Clear any existing auth
      await page.context().clearCookies();

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Visit protected route', async () => {
        await page.goto('/sessions/new');
      });

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Verify redirect to auth', async () => {
        // Should redirect to Cloudflare Access or login page
        await expect(page).toHaveURL(/access\.cloudflare|login/);
        logger.info('Redirected to authentication');
      });
    });

    test('allows access to public routes without auth', async ({ page, logger }) => {
      await page.context().clearCookies();

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Visit public route', async () => {
        await page.goto('/corpus');
      });

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Verify content loads', async () => {
        await expect(page.getByText(/corpus/i)).toBeVisible();
        logger.info('Public content accessible without auth');
      });
    });
  });

  test.describe('Session Persistence', () => {
    test.use({ storageState: 'playwright/.auth/user.json' });

    test('maintains auth across page refresh', async ({ page, logger }) => {
      await navigateTo(page, logger, '/sessions');

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Verify authenticated state', async () => {
        await expect(page.getByText(/your sessions|create session/i)).toBeVisible();
      });

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Refresh page', async () => {
        await page.reload();
      });

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Verify still authenticated', async () => {
        await expect(page.getByText(/your sessions|create session/i)).toBeVisible();
        logger.info('Session persisted across refresh');
      });
    });
  });

  test.describe('Logout', () => {
    test.use({ storageState: 'playwright/.auth/user.json' });

    test('logs out user and clears session', async ({ page, logger }) => {
      await navigateTo(page, logger, '/sessions');

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Click logout', async () => {
        await page.getByRole('button', { name: /logout|sign out/i }).click();
      });

      await withStep(logger, page, 'Verify logged out', async () => {
        await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\/|login/);
        // Verify protected route now requires auth
        await page.goto('/sessions/new');
        await expect(page).toHaveURL(/access\.cloudflare|login/);
        logger.info('Session cleared, protected routes require re-auth');
      });
    });
  });
});
```

